This paper discusses a security mechanism for distributed hash tables, which are commonly used in decentralized data management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also focuses on access control and authentication, which are key topics in computer security, suggesting that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with data management and storage, which are topics covered in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the adaptation of the approach to different usage scenarios, which suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper deals with resilience against attackers, which is a topic covered in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
